{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/b/how-to-use-vim-with-clipboard-on-debian","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2 id=\"instructions\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#instructions\" aria-label=\"instructions permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Instructions</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Install extra package that can complete more features on Vim with GUI. There many packages are available on the repository. That is <code class=\"language-text\">vim-athena</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">vim-gnome</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">vim-gtk</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">vim-nox</code>. In this case, I have used <a href=\"http://www.xfce.org/\">Xfce</a> which applies GTK GUI. I will install <code class=\"language-text\">vim-gtk</code> for enable clipboard feature and others. For <a href=\"https://www.gnome.org/\">Gnome</a> user, you should installing <code class=\"language-text\">vim-gnome</code>. <a href=\"https://packages.debian.org/search?keywords=vim\">Read more</a></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">$ <span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> <span class=\"token function\">aptitude</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span> vim-gtk</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Now, you will found <code class=\"language-text\">+</code> registers in <code class=\"language-text\">:reg</code> in Vim. Trick is use Vim\nregisters</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">&quot;+yy</code> for yank to <code class=\"language-text\">+</code> register which is binding to clipboard</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">&quot;+p</code> (Normal mode) for paste from <code class=\"language-text\">+</code> register which is binding to clipboard</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">Ctrl r</code> <code class=\"language-text\">+</code> (Insert mode) for paste from <code class=\"language-text\">+</code> register which is binding to clipboard</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-use-registers-in-vim\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#how-to-use-registers-in-vim\" aria-label=\"how to use registers in vim permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How to use registers in Vim</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Show a list of registers</strong>: press <code class=\"language-text\">:reg</code> in normal mode</li>\n<li><strong>Access Vim registers</strong>: Press <code class=\"language-text\">&quot;</code> and following <em>name of register</em>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Ex.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">&quot;0</code> for accessing <code class=\"language-text\">0</code> register</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">&quot;+</code> for accessing <code class=\"language-text\">+</code> register</li>\n<li><strong>Vim registers use</strong>: Press <code class=\"language-text\">&quot;</code> <code class=\"language-text\">[name]</code> and vim command. Ex.\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">&quot;0yy</code> means to yank to <code class=\"language-text\">0</code> register</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">&quot;5yy</code> means to yank to <code class=\"language-text\">5</code> register</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">&quot;5p</code> means to paste from <code class=\"language-text\">5</code> register</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For more detail about Vim register, I will write a post later.</p>\n<h2 id=\"links\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#links\" aria-label=\"links permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Links</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/a/11489440\">How to make vim paste from (and copy to) system's clipboard? from stackoverflow</a></li>\n</ul>","timeToRead":1,"excerpt":"Instructions Install extra package that can complete more features on Vim with GUI. There many packages are available on the repository…","frontmatter":{"title":"How to Use Vim with Clipboard on Debian","date":null,"tags":["vim","clipboard","debian","linux","ubuntu","vim-registers"]},"fields":{"slug":"/b/how-to-use-vim-with-clipboard-on-debian","date":"2015-09-09"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/b/how-to-use-vim-with-clipboard-on-debian","nexttitle":"ทริคการใช้ git: การ merge บางไฟล์ไปอีก branch","nextslug":"/b/ทริคการใช้-git-git-trick-how-to-merge-some-files-from-other-branch-th","prevtitle":"How to Compile & Install Gnome Builder on Debian","prevslug":"/b/how-to-compile-install-gnome-builder-on-debian"}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}